  "_doc": "Complex DFT showcase — five scan chains across two clock domains plus a dense surrounding datapath. Open the DFT panel to see the chain diagrams light up:\n  • chain_0 — HEALTHY, CLK_FAST domain (3 cells, full scan-in/out, shared TE_GLOBAL).\n  • chain_1 — HEALTHY, CLK_SLOW domain (3 cells, second clock, second TE source TE_BIST).\n  • chain_2 — WARN, split TE (2 cells, scan-in + scan-out fine, but each cell uses a different TE source — visible as a dashed amber bar).\n  • chain_3 — BROKEN, scan-out floating (2 cells wired to each other but the tail's Q goes nowhere — chain response unobservable).\n  • chain_4 — ORPHAN (a lone SCAN_FF with nothing wired into TI or Q — can never participate in any test).\nSurrounding logic exercises ≥15 different component types so the canvas reads like a real subsystem rather than a pure scan-island: ALU, COUNTER, LFSR, ROM, RAM, REGISTER, COMPARATOR, MUX_2, FULL_ADDER, DECODER, ENCODER, FF_SLOT, GATE_SLOT (AND/OR/XOR/NOT), CLOCK ×2, INPUT/OUTPUT.",
